{"id": "duc04-testb-23:1#4", "contents": "The austerity measures at the palace are part of a larger plan to reduce Brazil's budget deficit, which currently stands at $65 billion, or 7% of the country's economic output. Cardoso is expected to unveil the full scope of his deficit-cutting plan next week, which is believed to include new taxes on fuel, income, personal fortunes, and bank transactions. The plan is part of a deal with the International Monetary Fund (IMF) for a rescue package estimated at $30 billion. The goal of the plan is to restore investor confidence in Brazil's economy, which has been battered by the world financial turmoil."}
